WEBVTT

00:00.900 --> 00:06.080
There have been all sorts of ideas and schemes cooked up to try and clean up that oil spill.

00:06.080 --> 00:10.680
We found one that has nothing to do with giant sponges or even human hair.

00:10.680 --> 00:11.800
It's an engine.

00:11.800 --> 00:15.680
And as our business and tech reporter Scott Budman shows us, it runs on what's in the

00:15.680 --> 00:19.740
Gulf right now.

00:19.740 --> 00:26.360
With as much as 800,000 gallons of crude oil a day spilling into the Gulf, the situation

00:26.360 --> 00:27.680
is desperate.

00:27.680 --> 00:29.900
How do we get rid of all this oil?

00:29.900 --> 00:30.900
Here we go.

00:30.900 --> 00:39.680
Here's one idea, an engine that runs on a mix of 80% seawater and 20% oil, like what

00:39.680 --> 00:40.860
you see in the Gulf.

00:40.860 --> 00:42.940
This would be the right time to put this forward.

00:42.940 --> 00:46.720
Charles Ostman is a physicist helping to test the engine.

00:46.720 --> 00:50.740
He says it's not that complicated and that it could work.

00:50.740 --> 00:55.000
In my vision, I would see an array of these things on board, just feed the materials through

00:55.000 --> 00:57.060
there and keep pulling out useful materials.

00:57.060 --> 01:02.180
exactly what I'd be doing. The mix of oil and water burns cleaner than what's in our cars or

01:02.180 --> 01:11.340
lawnmowers. And it did burn clean for us up to a point. But maybe all of this will lead to more

01:11.340 --> 01:16.700
ideas like this. Maybe the bright side of this is that now finally people that would have never

01:16.700 --> 01:19.660
looked at this before saying wait a minute maybe there are those solutions let's give it a second

01:19.660 --> 01:25.520
try. So in my mind that's the positive side of this otherwise very dark circumstance. Bad news

01:25.520 --> 01:33.600
leading to inventors firing up new solutions in santa clara scott budman nbc bay area news

01:33.600 --> 01:38.160
the group that invented the oil and water engine contacted british petroleum

01:38.160 --> 01:40.420
VP wrote back saying, no thanks.

